apt already supports using torrents for p2p package distribution, via apt-p2p: https://launchpad.net/ubuntu/zesty/+package/apt-p2p (WARN: clearnet)

if you use a local nginx proxy, you could point the upstream at a local copy of a zeronet site, and use the downstream as a repo for any package manager with custom repo support (pacman, apt, etc)

i've never used chocolatey, but i imagine you could use the nginx hack if it supports custom repos.
